    "privileged_info_summary": "The task utilizes a real structure of yeast phenylalanine tRNA (PDB ID 1EHZ), downloaded directly from the RCSB Protein Data Bank. Programmatic parsing of the PDB atomic coordinates confirms the straight-line distance between the 3' terminal nucleotide (residue 76) and the middle anticodon nucleotide (residue 35) ranges from approximately 67 to 80 Å, correctly aligning with the verifier's acceptable bounds of 55.0 to 95.0 Å. Furthermore, analyzing the MODRES records in the 1EHZ.pdb file verifies the presence of the claimed modified nucleotides (e.g., PSU, H2U, OMC, OMG, YYG, 5MC, 7MG, 5MU, 1MA, M2G, as well as their full names like pseudouridine and wybutosine) within the structure.",
